Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // App losing focus (partially backgrounded)
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native event objects, override `OnStopped` on a `Window` subclass — it maps to `OnStop` on Android and `DidEnterBackground` on iOS automatically:

```csharp
public class AppWindow : Window
{
    public AppWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }

    protected override void OnStopped()
    {
        base.OnStopped();
        // Runs on all platforms when backgrounded
    }
}
```

Return it from `App.CreateWindow`:

```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
    => new AppWindow(new AppShell());
```

**Key tips:**
- `OnPause` (Android) ≈ `Deactivated` (focus lost, still visible). `OnStop`/`DidEnterBackground` ≈ `Stopped` (fully hidden).
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.
- On Android, also save state in `OnDestroying` — the back button can skip `Stopped`.
